                     user management
useradd < username >
passwd abk ( create password)
grep < user name > /etc/passwd ( account property )
grep < username > /etc/shadow ( check password )
su < username > ( switch username )
"exit" or "ctrl +d" ( logout )
sudo userdel -r < username >
usermod ( modify a user's account properties )

                  group management ( sudo su )

groupadd < group name > ( create group )  
cat /stc/group ( all group show )
grep < group name > /etc/shadow ( group admin property )
groupdel < group name > ( delete group )
gpasswd -a < username > < group name > ( add single user )
gpasswd -M < username > < username > < username > < group name > ( add Multiple user )
gpasswd -d < username > < username > ( remove user names )
gpasswd -A username groupname ( make group admin )

for check file permission
ls -l < file >.txt

 grep use
grep < word name > < file.txt > 
grep -i <word name > < file name > ( For Incesitive file )

  find use
find < directory > -< file name > 
( e.g. find /home -file.txt also you can find multiple files ->  find /home *txt) 

awk use 
its like a find command using for log file, table content
awk ' { print $1 }' < file name > or awk ' { awk { print $1, $2 } ' < file name >

head use
head /etc/passwd ( show 10 top line )
head -n 5 /etc/passwd ( show top line )

tail use
tail /etc/passwd ( show 10 tail line )
tail -n 5 /etc/passwd ( show tail line )

  vim use 
Undo & Redo
u & ctrl+r

Navigate vim 
h - left   k - up
i - right  j - down

Jump line
gg - first line               G - last line
:n - go to number of line

Editing line
i - insert mode        :w - save              :q! without save and exit
a - exit insert mode   :wq - save and exit

Delete
x ( Delete )
dd ( Delete Line )

Change colorpallate of vim 
:colorscheme < tab key >

( Benefit of vim )
speed, ease of use, light weight, Always Available, Customizable, Remotely Edit 
